</paragraph>
<paragraph id="55F9994F6982F8B9546F53DF3518D0B5" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
<taxonomicName id="39F5F17D515AF04F7A526EB02B3DDAD9" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Proctor" authorityYear="1967" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia subprocera" order="Myrtales" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subprocera">Conostegia subprocera</taxonomicName>
Proctor, Bull. Inst. Jam. Sci. ser. 16: 38. Pl. 16, p.40. 1967. Type: Jamaica. Portland Parish: east slope of John Crow Mts, c. 1-1.5 miles southwest of Ecclesdown, 1500 ft., 6 August 1954, G. R. Proctor 9229 (holotype: IJ).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D20E5DE70C4F648CC88D322C33A913CD" lastPageId="92" lastPageNumber="93" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" type="description">
<paragraph id="2D41B1F7F6AF7C468ACD8A7479F44738" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="012F09274307446CB76AD289C5D707E6" lastPageId="92" lastPageNumber="93" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
Shrubs to small trees 1-5 m tall with subtetragonal stems that become terete and that are densely beset with simple roughened to dendritic trichomes near the tips, a small layer of inconspicuous underdeveloped dendritic trichomes also present, glabrescent to glabrous with age; the nodal line present, covered or not by indument on young branches. Leaves of a pair equal to somewhat unequal in length. Petiole 0.5-3.5 cm, adaxially pubescent like the stem apices. Leaf blade 4-13 
<normalizedToken id="6CA240F320812A4923EC589A3C009457" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-5 cm, 3-nerved, oblong, linear to elliptic or ovate to obovate, the base acute to rounded, the apex rounded to acute or acuminate, the margin entire, the adaxial surface glabrous, the abaxial surface essentially glabrous, sometimes with short stipitate and sessile stellate 
<pageBreakToken id="0CA319443EBDEBA7F195B16BD366B94B" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" start="start">trichomes</pageBreakToken>
on the mid vein and some secondary veins and inconspicuously glandular puncticulate throughout. Inflorescence a terminal panicle 3-8.5 cm long branched above the base, accessory branches apparently absent, bracts and bracteoles 0.5-2 mm, subulate, deciduous. Pedicel 7-13 mm. Flowers 5-7 merous, calyptrate. Floral buds 11-20 mm long, ovoid, the base obtuse to rounded, the apex acute and mucronate, not constricted, the hypanthium 6-7 
<normalizedToken id="EA776E50738618A2E88D0D905DA854ED" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6-7 mm, smooth and glabrous. Petals 6-17 mm long, white. Stamens 11-18, 6-8 mm long, the filaments 3.4-4.4 mm long, white, lacking a conspicuous geniculation, anthers 3-4 
<normalizedToken id="BC7DD95CA836034A25B499A64757EABC" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.8-1 mm, subulate, recurved at the tip, yellow, somewhat laterally compressed, the pore ca. 0.1 mm wide, terminal. Ovary 5-7 locular, inferior, apically glabrous and forming a collar around the style base. Style ca. 8-9 mm, straight to slightly bent at the tip, vertical distance from the anther to the stigma -0-1 mm, horizontal distance absent, the stigma truncate, ca. 04-0.5 mm wide. Berry ca. 10 
<normalizedToken id="54AFCE44B56BE3372C2FD93698C7FB9C" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
10 mm, red at first but turning purple black with maturity. Seeds ca 0.8 mm, pyramidal, smooth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B273884E3E90F9A3CD3CA135BB2B6E97" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="06123138C098F6D311EA7B56D65CC84E" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">
<pageBreakToken id="FC87C14D1F5DDFDDF975D0FAAE64DDED" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" start="start">Distribution</pageBreakToken>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F494300494EC84A8D635A3EB64CA36FC" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="ACFA424D6B4F540F74F977B8C2E50C5C" captionStart="Figure 100" captionStartId="F100" captionText="Figure 100. Distribution of Conostegia pyxidata." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure100" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96458" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">100</figureCitation>
). Endemic to Jamaica, 200-1100 m in elevation.
</paragraph>
<caption id="8FBD0E645CAB8BEA980253C876B5BC6F" ID-Zenodo-Dep="973840" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure100" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96458" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" start="Figure 100" startId="F100">
<paragraph id="EBFFA1A3DDC95E9C3EE93DF6EAFDA7BB" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis id="7ADADC499BC6177836EEA21EA8EB0236" bold="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Figure 100.</emphasis>
Distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="67C3A3FD544C566597D0CC113AF3AE88" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Proctor" authorityYear="1967" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia pyxidata" order="Myrtales" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pyxidata">
<emphasis id="D5A436F611AB6B1E3B4EF5533B662F88" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Conostegia pyxidata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="0ED643ECBD542CB90621FE68CD1EE8A7" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">
<bibRefCitation id="E7B317F8C84A11A912FD2BAE52D20167" author="Schnell, CE" journalOrPublisher="Harvard University" pageId="243" pageNumber="244" refId="B77" refString="Schnell, CE, 1996. The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae). Harvard University" title="The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae)" year="1996">Schnell (1996)</bibRefCitation>
discusses at length that 
<taxonomicName id="7E37AADE8321E6597FEDFD10795880FE" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Proctor" authorityYear="1967" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia pyxidata" order="Myrtales" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pyxidata">
<emphasis id="1D178D04ED84A1821DFF2EDE53A1DB91" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Conostegia pyxidata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="2DA77623BBDEF9AB17AA5F0B3C338739" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia balbisiana" order="Myrtales" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="balbisiana">
<emphasis id="85BD745F253B1C1CC1698EC5225987B7" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Conostegia balbisiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="8D029DEA27428282A193098404AB6CCB" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia procera" order="Myrtales" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="procera">
<emphasis id="67AC12E63B4974269FF08E1AC64F3559" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Conostegia procera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. He chose to maintain the species on a 
<normalizedToken id="9D1D58C8EF744670713B69B99F562642" originalValue="“borderline”">&quot;borderline&quot;</normalizedToken>
decision and gave three reasons for keeping the three taxa as distinct: 1) some morphological differences in a small area; 2) the disjunct range of 
<taxonomicName id="68A173117CFF184BB50AAA99CD54729E" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia balbisiana" order="Myrtales" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="balbisiana">
<emphasis id="B49F5013AB514A36CE90697566C5868E" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Conostegia balbisiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; and 3) differences in flowering time between the more similar species 
<taxonomicName id="B6D9C8B1E8AC7FBFE33A07CD6392E62A" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia procera" order="Myrtales" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="procera">
<emphasis id="69F7C0A2A7364871FCF35AB2DE1C18D2" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Conostegia procera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="01E87C26F204DAFE8E2CBCB151F8F927" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Proctor" authorityYear="1967" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia pyxidata" order="Myrtales" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pyxidata">
<emphasis id="B66D9F56811611670442145A81F4477F" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Conostegia pyxidata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="B2ECCA19AE2FEEABB0D49691A3AFFE4E" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia balbisiana" order="Myrtales" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="balbisiana">
<emphasis id="E0C0F2C73E50A3E846F73A0BA450B346" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Conostegia balbisiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
overlapping somewhat in flowering time with the other two species, but having larger flowers with different stamen morphology. 
<bibRefCitation id="6F6C602AD387B3E161B055E54DBA0EA9" author="Schnell, CE" journalOrPublisher="Harvard University" pageId="243" pageNumber="244" refId="B77" refString="Schnell, CE, 1996. The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae). Harvard University" title="The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae)" year="1996">Schnell (1996)</bibRefCitation>
argued that these morphological and phenological differences suggested the presence of biological isolation and a diverging lineage. For the time being I have chosen to follow 
<normalizedToken id="251021BD88B9369AB80736A02C93070D" originalValue="Schnell’s">Schnell's</normalizedToken>
reasoning for recognizing three taxa. 
<bibRefCitation id="BDD1F08CB9FDFC0118260D1C00D38B10" author="Schnell, CE" journalOrPublisher="Harvard University" pageId="243" pageNumber="244" refId="B77" refString="Schnell, CE, 1996. The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae). Harvard University" title="The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae)" year="1996">Schnell (1996)</bibRefCitation>
also suggested the possibility of introgression from 
<taxonomicName id="1FA7FA440C59D89A9CA194AB14C2F7C2" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1850" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia rufescens" order="Myrtales" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis id="26554D0D30747EDDE5FD98FAC360D611" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Conostegia rufescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The type of 
<taxonomicName id="2476E3C23CC49749CC53A8A836BDD2DB" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Proctor" authorityYear="1967" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia subprocera" order="Myrtales" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subprocera">
<emphasis id="BE1B8C0517415859D456667AC55B876D" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Conostegia subprocera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was not studied but 
<bibRefCitation id="4BC6B3C17EA4AAD0B95C6DDBBD9072A4" author="Schnell, CE" journalOrPublisher="Harvard University" pageId="243" pageNumber="244" refId="B77" refString="Schnell, CE, 1996. The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae). Harvard University" title="The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae)" year="1996">Schnell (1996)</bibRefCitation>
cited this name as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="CFE239DF9E788E76A55222E1FC2314ED" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Proctor" authorityYear="1967" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia pyxidata" order="Myrtales" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pyxidata">
<emphasis id="4D678655BDEF6F29357E34FFFBF6B242" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Conostegia pyxidata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
